# Chess-Mate Agent Reference

Before making any changes to this application, read `/Users/davidreichardt/chess-mate/AGENTS.md`.

It is the single source of truth for:
- Project structure and where files belong
- Routing, layouts, and which layout to use for new pages
- State management (Zustand stores, TanStack Query usage)
- The lesson system and static data conventions
- Design system tokens (colors, spacing, typography, shadows)
- Chess board highlight/arrow/challenge system
- Component inventory and page completion status
- Key conventions (imports, TypeScript, naming)
- Known limitations — what is and isn't wired to the backend

Also read `frontend/DESIGN.md` before making any UI or styling changes.
